actionDT'] // 3600) % 24` or similar. Since we don't know the exact offset of day 0, any cyclical features might still align nicely with repeating 24-hour cycles.\n\nLet's test these features in Python and see their correlation with `isFraud` or their feature importance using a quick XGBoost model.\",\n  \"plan\": \"1. Write a python test script `test_features.py` that computes these features, trains a baseline model, and measures temporal CV or train/test split AUC.\\n2. We will run the script and inspect the output.\",\n  \"commands\": [\n    {\n      \"keystrokes\": \"cat \u003c\u003c 'EOF' \u003e test_features.py\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport numpy as np\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score\\nimport xgboost as xgb\\n\\n# Load data\\ndf = pd.read_csv('/data/transactions.csv')\\ndf = df.sort_values('TransactionDT').reset_index(drop=True)\\n\\n# Feature Engineering\\nprint(\\\"Engineering features...\\\")\\n\\n# 1. Time velocity features\\ndf['dt_diff_card1'] = df.groupby('card1')['TransactionDT'].diff().fillna(-1)\\ndf['dt_diff_card1_addr1'] = df.groupby(['card1', 'addr1'])['TransactionDT'].diff().fillna(-1)\\n\\n# 2. Cumulative frequency/count features\\ndf['card1_cum_count'] = df.groupby('card1').cumcount()\\ndf['card1_addr1_cum_count'] = df.groupby(['card1', 'addr1']).cumcount()\\n\\n# 3. Cumulative amount statistics\\n# Shift to avoid lookahead/leakage\\ndf['card1_amt_cum_mean'] = df.groupby('card1')['TransactionAmt'].transform(lambda x: x.shift().expanding().mean()).fillna(-1)\\ndf['card1_addr1_amt_cum_mean'] = df.groupby(['card1', 'addr1'])['TransactionAmt'].transform(lambda x: x.shift().expanding().mean()).fillna(-1)\\n\\n# 4. Cyclical time features\\n# Let's see if 24-hour cycles exist\\ndf['hour'] = (df['TransactionDT'] // 3600) % 24\\n\\n# 5. Amount relative to historical average\\ndf['amt_to_mean_card1'] = df['TransactionAmt'] / (df['card1_amt_cum_mean'] + 1e-5)\\n\\n# Categorical feature encoding\\ndf = pd.get_dummies(df, columns=['ProductCD'],